Gunmen have killed Saheed Lawal, a point of sales (POS) operator in the Bako area of Ibadan, the Oyo State capital. Lawal was killed on Friday night shortly after returning home. TheCable reports that three armed men stormed his house at about 7.30 pm and shot him in the chest at a close range in the presence of his wife. It was learnt that the killers came on a motorcycle. “The deceased, about 40-year-old, was shot at close range in his house a few minutes after returning home from the mosque,” a community leader was quoted as saying. - Advertisement - “Lawal was a POS operator in the community and financial secretary of the area’s landlord association.   Police detain ‘abducted’ Ebonyi PDP Publicity…     Ekiti 2022: Fayose, Olujimi camps reconcile     Labour begins mass mobilisation for subsidy removal protests   “The suspected robbers were three in number, they came on a motorcycle. “Two of them positioned themselves close to the deceased residence while one of them knocked at his entrance door. “As Lawal was opening the door, the robber opened fire on his chest at a close range.” The source added that the killers also met the victim’s wife, who begged them not to kill his husband. “Unknown to the wife that her husband had been killed, she was begging them not to kill him. They asked for money, and she gave them what she had. “It was after the robbers had left that she saw her husband in a pool of his blood,” he added. The report says two of the killers escaped on the motorcycle that brought them — while the other that was stranded scared residents away with gunshots and escaped through a nearby bush.